MESSAGE.value: Added some mechanisms for adding human observation nodes to the graphs.
Have game player interface up, with silly one-question baseline. Now have to go track down bug with inference.
Fixed bugs with game player, so now runs, just gets the wrong result
added small test to peel apart game player a bit
now seems to work to add observed variables to the graph. Needed to add hard factors to the observed variables to get influence to be noticed.
Good enough for now, have a way to set variables to constant during inference, and to leave them floating correctly during learning.
Still tinkering with learning weights without screwing everything up
Now beating baseline by just learning super simple class priors.
Basic one question baseline + bias learning beats no learning baseline by 6 points.
Got baselines running, one move lookahead game player is put together
Numeric stability issues with Factorie and very large sparse sets of weights.
Making le changes
Multiple calls to learning doesn't restart cleanly. Disaster
Minor aesthetic updates to GraphStream, now need to go make a GUI or something for watching game players in real time.
Early Results!! Beating baselines. Fuck yeah!!
Reformatting results page for clarity and email-ability
Adding a history of game trajectories to the Lense object, started the Lanterna GUI to review them.
Stubbing out a Java2D GUI to try to make it easier to debug loss functions and learning routines.
Moving human responses into a Future, so that we can have a server handle more of this.
Fabulous, have a simple self-contained server set up and integrated with IntelliJ. Now to make a real Q/A system...
Appear to have guts of an async socket in place. Now need to figure out how it works.
Think I've figured out roughly how to make this all work. Now I need to go write some question formats.
Added a work unit queue, and some machinery for dispatching work to different annotators in-browser.
Finally have websocket talking properly with server. Will soon fix up interrupted connections.
Working on a workaround for detecting connection closing.
